description: This file is the main entry point for a React application using ReactDOM to render the root component wrapped in React.StrictMode and BrowserRouter.

methods.name: ReactDOM.createRoot
methods.description: Creates a root for rendering a React component tree in the specified DOM element.

methods.name: <React.StrictMode>
methods.description: A wrapper that activates additional checks and warnings for its children in development mode.

methods.name: BrowserRouter
methods.description: Provides routing context for navigation in a React application.

methods.name: ReactDOM.createRoot.render
methods.description: Renders the React element tree into the DOM.
